Package com.percussion.cms.objectstore

Interface Summary
IPSBinaryLocator This interface facilitates the access of binary data from the server.
IPSCmsComponent This interface must be implemented by all objects used in the CMS layer that need to be serialized to/from xml.
IPSComponentProcessor Classes implementing this interface are responsible for providing the capability to save, load and remove CMS components to/from the database.
IPSDbComponent The CMS objectstore represents CMS concepts such as folders and slots as Java objects.
IPSFieldValue Base interface for any type of value contained by an PSItemField.
IPSItemAccessor Provides access interface to the implementing object.
IPSRelationshipProcessor The relationship processor defines the methods needed to manage relationships between objects defined in the Object table.
IPSVisitor Implemented by objects that are accepted by the IPSItemAccessor.
 

Class Summary
PSAaRelationship This class adds a few methods that are specific to Active Assembly category of relationships to make it more convenient and easy to manipulate active assembly relationships.
PSAaRelationshipList A collection of PSAaRelationship objects.
PSAction The class that is used to represent menu actions as defined by 'sys_Action.dtd'.
PSActionParameters The class that is used to represent properties as defined by 'sys_Params.dtd'.
PSActionProperties The class that is used to represent properties as defined by 'sys_Props.dtd'.
PSActionVisibilityContexts Title:
PSActiveAssemblyProcessorProxy This class extends PSProcessorProxy and is to manipulate all the active assembly relationships and properties and is a convenient wrapper around the functionality of PSRelationshipProcessorProxy with methods that are meaningful for active assembly processing.
PSBinaryValue This class holds the value as binary.
PSChildActions The class that is used to represent properties as defined by 'sys_Props.dtd'.
PSCmsComponent Implements some of the methods in the IPSComponent interface that don't vary across all or many of the components that will be implemented in the CMS layer.
PSCmsObject An object representation of a row in the PSX_OBJECTS table.
PSCmsProperty This class is responsible for managing a single name/value pairing known as a property.
PSComponentDefProcessorProxy This class is similar to PSComponentProcessorProxy in the way it functions, however it deals with the CMS design objects such as Content Type, Slot, Variant, Workflow definitions etc.
PSComponentProcessorProxy This class presents the interfaces supported by the processor classes, but doesn't actually perform any work.
PSComponentSummaries The PSComponentSummaries is a container class which contains a set of PSComponentSummary objects
PSComponentSummary The PSComponentSummary contains some item information that is from a row in the CONTENTSTATUS table.
PSContentType An object representation of a row in the CONTENTTYPES table.
PSContentTypeSet This class is a thin wrapper of the PSDbComponentSet that represents a set of PSContentType objects.
PSContentTypeVariant Deprecated. Use the assembly service to load and manipulate variant information
PSContentTypeVariantSet Deprecated. Use the assembly service to load and manipulate variant information
PSCoreItem The base class for items in the CMS layer.
PSDateValue The value of an PSItemField that is treated as a date value.
PSDbComponent Base class for all IPSDbComponents.
PSDbComponentCollection This class allows management of a set of IPSDbComponents.
PSDbComponentList See base class for details.
PSDbComponentSet This class allows management of a set of IPSDbComponents.
PSDFColumns See base class for details.
PSDFProperties See base class PSDbComponentList for details.
PSDisplayFormat Represents a single display format object defined by the system.
PSFieldValue Base class for all IPSFieldValue.
PSFolder This class contains all the persistant information for a folder object.
PSFolderAcl This class represents a PSObjectAcl for a folder.
PSFolderPermissions This class computes the user's permission on a folder object.
PSFolderProperty This property class is used by the PSFolder class.
PSItemChild An object representation of the StandardItem.xsd Child element.
PSItemChildEntry An object representation of the sys_StandardItem.xsd ChildEntry element.
PSItemComponent All IPSDbComponents associated with an item must derive from this class.
PSItemDefExtractor This class extracts definition data for PSCoreItem object population.
PSItemDefinition  
PSItemDefSummary An item definition contains all of the design elements that define what an item is.
PSItemField An object representation of the StandardItem.xsd Field element.
PSItemFieldMeta An object representation of the StandardItem FieldMeta element.
PSItemRelatedItem An object representation of the StandardItem RelatedItem element.
PSKey This class is used to store a multi-part identifier for a component.
PSMultiValuedProperty This class is designed to support properties that have multiple values, each value stored as a row in the same table in the database.
PSObjectAcl The class represents a collection of ACL entries.
PSObjectPermissions This class contains all the logic for determining the level of access a user has on a specified object.
PSProcessingStatistics This class contains the results from a processing request.
PSProcessorCommon This is the base class for a set of processors that use applications to perform their work.
PSProcessorProxy This class presents the interfaces supported by the processor classes, but doesn't actually perform any work.
PSRelationshipFilter This class allows one to specify filtering criteria when querying for relationships by the implementer of the interface IPSRelationshipProcessor.
PSRelationshipInfo This is a read only class, it contains partial information of a specific relationship configuration.
PSRelationshipInfoSet The PSRelationshipInfoSet contains a list of PSRelationshipInfo objects
PSRelationshipProcessorProxy This class presents the interfaces supported by the processor classes, but doesn't actually perform any work.
PSSaveResults This class wraps a set of results returned by a processor.
PSSearch Represents a single search/view as defined within the system.
PSSFields A simple wrapper around PSDbComponentList that simplifies use by providing the class name of the class is stored in the list.
PSSimpleKey This class is used for 1 part keys.
PSSlot The slot is basically a container for other items with particular formatting (variants).
PSSlotType The PSSlotType represents one row of the RXSLOTTYPE table.
PSSlotTypeContentTypeVariant This read-only DB component represents one row from the RXSLOTCONTENT table.
PSSlotTypeContentTypeVariantSet This is variant slot collection class, which is a dependent class of the PSContentTypeVariant.
PSSlotTypeSet This class is a thin wrapper of the PSDbComponentSet that represents a set of PSSlotType objects.
PSSProperties See base class PSDbComponentList for details.
PSTextValue The value of an PSItemField that is treated as a String value.
PSVariantSlotType Deprecated. use the assembly service instead
PSVariantSlotTypeSet Deprecated. use the assembly service instead
PSXmlValue The value of an PSItemField that is treated as an XML element.
